<br>
Had been away from EQ for a while at lvl 55 and got back about a month ago. Was stuck at 55 for some time till PoP finally arrived and am loving finding groups again <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I made some money on my return and decided to save up for a CoF. Had around 25k when a 65 warrior friend told me of this awesome aggro weapon called a Greatstaff of Thunder( 2hb 31/30 +10ac+10dex+10agi+85hp+15svm, proc. Planar Stun)<br>
<br>
I was no stranger to 2hb as I have a ToD, but was rather sceptical about the ability of a 2hander to holding aggro really well. I had a Tae Ew ls (12/20) mh and FB offhand and that seemed to work ok.<br>
<br>
Then one fine day I saw the staff in the bazaar for 25k and gave it a shot. I jumped straight in and ended up in an exp group in PoI factory. The results were amazing. Give it a few seconds to build aggro or proc it's stun and the mob sticks to you like glue. I was getting summoned more than the shaman. <br>
The Sk said I had uber taunt sniff<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Later on I went to Kael arena with monk and shaman. If the monk ever did get aggro a simple taunt was enough to get it back. <br>
<br>
Tanked Phinney with it later on, again np. <br>
<br>
From what my lvl 65 warrior friend tells me this staff works better than his willsapper or a Fleshgrinder or whatever other 1hs out there that cost a fortune. <br>
<br>
Seems 1h and DW really are dying, at least for us non epic/EB wielding warriors as now both Dps and aggro can be done with 2handers.<br>
<br>
Only problem is the look of the staff <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
I mean it looks like I am poking a mob with something I made out of an old tyre lining and syphon taped together, not an all powerfull hate inducing, meanlooking, jagged blade type thing a warrior would want to be seen with<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/nerd.gif ALT="8o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
To all wars out there I advise you to try it too and thank you Hereward for yet another sound piece of advice on gear selection.<br>
<br>
